summary: Hey guys! We're excited to announce that one of our zine artists, Erica D'urso, has just finished her debut drawing volume 4 of...
body:
Hey guys! We’re excited to announce that one of our zine artists, Erica D'urso, has just finished her debut drawing volume 4 of the official Life of Captain Marvel comics!!!

We’re so excited to have her as a part of the zine and just as excited to see her work and her name next to such a well known franchise!

You can buy the comic HERE for a measly $3.99 and if you’d like to support Erica and thank her for all her hard work or see more of her gorgeous artwork, you can find her on twitter HERE !!!

title: 20 October 2018 (#658)
body:
My trip to the comic shop was a success, even though I did not get any Wynonna Earp comics. I was going through the IDW comics and saw next to them comics from Boom Studios. As I was going through them I got the first four trade paper backs for Lumberjanes! Of course I could not let this opportunity pass me by. I have read enough amazing reviews of these comics that I just had to buy them all.

I also picked up another Captain Marvel trade paper back. This time it was Captain Marvel Carol Danvers with the cool byline ‘The Ms. Marvel Years’. This one contains over 17 comics of Ms Marvel from 2006. Hopefully this one along with the others gives me enough of a background in Captain Marvel before the movie early next year.

Now to get back to Daredevil on Netflix….

caption:
SHAZAM! TP NEW EDITION

written by GEOFF JOHNS
art by GARY FRANK
photo cover
Brought to the feet of the magical wizard Shazam at the Rock of Eternity, Billy Batson is imbued with powers beyond any mortal man. By shouting the wizard’s name—Shazam!—the young teen is mystically transformed into the powerhouse known as Captain Marvel! Now given abilities that make him Earth’s Mightiest Mortal at the utterance of a simple phrase, will Billy make the right choices and do what it takes to become a hero? Or will he succumb to the poor choices of youth—and the villainous Black Adam?
Collects Justice League #0 and 21 and backup stories from issues #7-11, 14-16 and 18-20 with a photo cover from the upcoming Warner Bros. film starring Zachary Levi!

summary: okay so we all know that Howard Stark was an abusive piece of shit, but I feel like some people don’t really actually understand...
caption:
okay so we all know that Howard Stark was an abusive piece of shit, but I feel like some people don’t really actually understand how much he hurt tony?

And I feel like this single quote outlines it perfectly. Tony’s just seen his father get brutally murdered, repeatedly punched and left to die. Same with his mother, but her death is actually far less gruesome and is shown way less. 

And the only person he cares about? His mother. He literally just saw his father die in front of his eyes, and he doesn’t care. He could have easily said “he killed my parents”. But he doesn’t. Do you know how little you have to care when you see someone get murdered in front of you?

He wants to avenge his mother’s death. That’s why he wanted to hurt Bucky. But he doesn’t care about his father. He wanted to avenge his mother. He didn’t care that Howard was killed. 

Can you imagine what Howard must have done to warrant that kind of indifference? The opposite of love isn’t hate. It’s indifference. Tony Stark just saw his father get murdered in front of him, and he does. not. care.

summary: How do you feel about Hulking ( Dorrek VIII,"Teddy" Altman) being Mar-Vell’s son? It was a kind of big deal during the last...
caption: How do you feel about Hulking ( Dorrek VIII,“Teddy” Altman) being Mar-Vell’s son? It was a kind of big deal during the last issues of the first run of Young Avengers, and a bit during Secret Invasion (with Khn’nr), and his half kree-half skrull origin was kind of tackled a bit during Al Ewing’s New Avengers. In general it has been kind of forgotten for the rest of the time, and being such a big issue with Genis and Phyla but not that important for him, I don’t know, I just feel that it could have been an interesting point for some stories but they usually just go with the half skrull part and his relationship with Billy.
